{
  "corpus": "notes",
  "about": [
    "Each question names every note needed to answer it (needs_notes) and, for each",
    "fact it must produce, a canary: a token the model cannot say unless it really",
    "read that note. A surname, a code, a figure — never something it could",
    "paraphrase or guess. answer_contains is a list of facts; each fact is a list of",
    "acceptable spellings. ALL the facts must appear, ANY spelling will do.",
    "",
    "kind=linked : BM25 alone cannot supply every note the question needs, so the",
    "              graph has to. This is what the expansion exists for, and the eval",
    "              checks the premise rather than trusting it: a linked question BM25",
    "              can already answer whole is a corpus fault, not a win.",
    "kind=direct : BM25 should find everything unaided. These are the control. The",
    "              expansion must not lose them — a direct question that regresses is",
    "              the noise failure mode, paid for in context it did not need.",
    "",
    "A question needing more than one note is a MULTI-NOTE question. It is not a",
    "third kind: it is simply len(needs_notes) > 1, and it is the hard case, because",
    "reaching both notes is necessary and no longer sufficient — the model has to",
    "carry a fact out of each and join them."
  ],
